Reasoning: The paper deals with image analysis and classification using machine learning techniques. Specifically, it focuses on the comparison of traditional texture feature extraction techniques with deep features extracted from convolution neural networks. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of deep learning models for feature extraction and classification suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of information retrieval techniques for feature extraction, which could potentially fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the mention of bone texture characterization suggests the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM).
